## G.28 Deep-seed — recipes as habits

Reading these recipes once is not enough. Practice them.

Next bug you hit, consciously walk the appropriate recipe. Do not skip steps. Do not guess. Follow the sequence.

After ten bugs, the recipes are habits. After twenty, they are reflexes. After fifty, you do not consciously think about which recipe applies — the right introspection call comes out of your fingers.

That reflex is the debugging speedup. It compounds.

