## G.48 Deep-seed — cross-referencing with Cortex

If you debug a lot in one project, save your bug hunts to Cortex. Every fix is a training pair for your future self:

```scheme
(cortex/record
  :subject 'bug
  :predicate 'fixed
  :object (list :symptom \"...\" :root-cause \"...\" :fix \"...\")
  :at (current-second)
  :source 'debug-session)
```

Query later:

```scheme
(cortex/query :subject 'bug :predicate 'fixed)
;; every fix you have ever made in this project
```

That is a personal bug knowledge base, built from Cortex + introspection. Grows with every session.

