## G.51 Deep-seed — the persistent lesson

Every recipe in this appendix comes down to the same idea: the runtime knows more than you do. Ask it. Do not guess.

Every guess is expensive. Every ask is cheap. The economy of debugging favors asking.

That is the whole recipe. Everything else is application.

## G.52 A closing thought

If the book gave you one thing, let it be this: when a bug surprises you, do not think first. Introspect first. The thinking comes after the data is on stdout.

That reflex saves hours per week over a career.

