## G.55 Deep-seed — a completely final observation on debugging philosophy

Some languages treat debugging as a separate mode. You compile, you run, you debug — three distinct phases with different tools. Motoi does not. Every debugging tool is a verb; every verb is available at any time; every debugging session is just the usual REPL with the introspection reflex engaged.

This unification is what makes Motoi debugging cheap in cognitive load. You do not have to switch mental models to enter debugging. You just start introspecting.

